So, what’s really going on? #TSRInvestigates w/ #JustinCarter

#PressPlay: Get y’all popcorn ready, Chance the Rapper’s new movie drops today in theaters across the country! “Chance the Rapper’s Magnificent Coloring World” marks the first time an artist has independently distributed a film to theatres.
________
“Magnificent Coloring World” is a concert film self-distributed through Chance the Rapper’s House of Kicks production company and film house.
________
Chance wrote, produced, edited and starred in the film, working hard this past year to bring never-before-seen footage to his fans. The footage was filmed in 2017 right before Chance took home 3 Grammys for his critically acclaimed mixtape “Coloring Book.”
________
Fans will be able to see the film in person for a limited time in several cities including Los Angeles, New York, Chicago, Detori, Las Vegas and Philly.

node.title: Chance The Rapper’s Film Released Today

node.text:
TSR Staff: Cassandra S. @__casmarie 
_______________________________
#TSRTunez: Whew! It seems like #CertifiedLoverBoy is giving what it's suppose to give! The album was released shortly after midnight on Friday. In the time since, #Drake's new tracks have led him to two broken records. 
_______________________________
According to @billboard, the Toronto rapper secured #AppleMusic's record for "most streamed album in a single day." Not only that, the streaming service also told Billboard that Drake is now their "most streamed artist" in 24 hours, at least for this year so far. 
_______________________________
Billboard's reporting did not specify the number of streams #CLB has received. However, the 21-track project has been the talk among social media users all day.
_______________________________
The project arrived after a few delays earlier this year. In January, he pushed back the release to dedicate his energy on recovering from—Read More At TheShadeRoom.Com! (📸: @gettyimages)

#TSRUpdatez: #Roommates, the fight for justice for #DaunteWright isn't over. It's just beginning. Former Minnesota officer #KimPotter who was facing second-degree manslaughter for fatally shooting #DaunteWright during a traffic stop in April, charges have been upgraded thanks to the public’s outcry.
__________________________
According to @foxnews, Minnesota Attorney General #KeithEllison added a first-degree manslaughter charge to Kim’s current charges. His office made the announcement yesterday and stated she allegedly recklessly handled her handgun. #Roomies, we will keep yall updated as more information becomes available! (SWIPE)

node.text:
Fans seem divided about #RKelly being listed as a writer on #Drake’s new album, ‘Certified Lover Boy.’
_______
According to @HotNewHipHop, the credit is attributed to a sample of Kelly’s that Drake used for his song ‘TSU.’ The song in question is reportedly R. Kelly’s ‘Half on a Baby.’
_______
While some fans are questioning Drake’s choice to use an R. Kelly sample, others argue that Kelly’s impact is difficult to get away from considering the volume of music he has produced and contributed to. What are your thoughts, #Roomies? (SWIPE) 📸: @gettyimages
